mber of transactions within the configured time window per user.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior targets counting/window logic in the scoring model and can be reproduced with fixed in-memory transactions and timestamps. No real infrastructure is required by the behavior text. Integration was considered and rejected because the text does not require DB/query-module interaction, only correct counting within a window.","test_description":"Invoke the velocity-check function with synthetic per-user transaction timestamps around window boundaries; assert exact counts, inclusive/exclusive cutoff handling, and per-user isolation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.76,"Integration":0.21,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A transaction flagged by the risk model but not by the scoring model is still held for review — the models operate as an OR gate, not AND.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This failure appears at module handoff/orchestration: combining outputs from two model components into a hold decision. Unit tests of a bare boolean helper are insufficient to catch wiring/mapping mistakes between modules. No real OS/network/subprocess is required, and correctness does not depend on real AI output content because model outputs can be deterministic fixtures for this behavior.","test_description":"Wire scoring-model adapter + risk-model adapter + decision service with in-process fakes; feed (score_flag=false, risk_flag=true) and assert transaction state becomes HOLD_FOR_REVIEW. Add symmetric case (true,false) and control case (false,false).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The combined output includes both the numeric risk score and the risk model's fraud probability, so the reviewer can see which model flagged the transaction and why.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior validates cross-module aggregation/contract: output must carry fields from both model results in one reviewer-facing payload. A pure unit test of a mapper may miss real wiring/serialization omissions. System was considered and rejected because real HTTP/OS/subprocess is not required to reproduce this failure; Agentic was rejected because this checks presence/propagation of outputs, not model-quality correctness.","test_description":"Exercise the service layer that invokes both model components (stubbed deterministic outputs) and builds reviewer payload; assert payload contains numeric_score, fraud_probability, and flag provenance fields for each model.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.31,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
